# =================================================================================================
# Nx Cache Directory Configuration
# =================================================================================================
#
# This file specifies a custom directory for Nx to store its cache files.
# This is particularly useful for storing cache outside of cloud-synced directories
# like OneDrive, which can cause performance issues and unnecessary sync operations.
#
# USAGE:
#   1. Copy this file to `.nx-cache-config` (without the .example extension)
#   2. Set the cache directory path below
#   3. The path can be absolute or relative to the workspace root
#   4. Source the setup script before running Nx commands:
#      - Linux/macOS/WSL: source ./scripts/nx-setup-cache.sh
#      - Windows (Git Bash): source ./scripts/nx-setup-cache.sh
#
# EXAMPLES:
#   - Absolute path (Windows): NX_CACHE_DIR=C:/dev-cache/nx-cache
#   - Absolute path (Linux/macOS): NX_CACHE_DIR=/home/user/dev-cache/nx-cache
#   - Relative path: NX_CACHE_DIR=../nx-cache-external
#
# NOTES:
#   - The directory will be created automatically if it doesn't exist
#   - Make sure the path is accessible and has proper write permissions
#   - The cache directory path should NOT be inside a cloud-synced folder
#   - Add your custom cache directory to .gitignore
#
# =================================================================================================

# Set your custom cache directory path here
# Default: uses Nx's default cache directory (.nx/cache in the workspace)
NX_CACHE_DIR=
NX_CACHE_DIR=/tmp/test-nx-cache
